            if (isRealisticMode) {
                if (isPhoto) {
                    if (transformType === 'realistic') finalPrompt = "**CRITICAL TASK: Hyper-Realistic 3D Character Transformation (Final Fantasy VII Remake Quality).**\n\n**Goal:** Transform the people in the provided photograph into a hyper-realistic, cinematic 3D character render. The final output MUST look like a state-of-the-art 3D model from a modern cinematic video game, with the quality standard of **Final Fantasy VII Remake**.\n\n**Technical Requirements (Strictly Enforced):**\n1.  **3D Modeling & Detail (Top Priority):** The 3D model must be of extremely high quality and detail, comparable to the main characters in FF7 Remake. Pay meticulous attention to facial structure, skin texture (pores, subtle imperfections), and realistic anatomy. The result MUST be a 3D render, NOT a 2D painting or drawing.\n2.  **Cinematic Lighting & Shadows (CRITICAL):** The lighting is paramount. It must be professional, cinematic, and dramatic, replicating the sophisticated lighting systems seen in FF7 Remake. Use techniques like three-point lighting, strong key lights to create defined, soft shadows, and prominent rim lighting to sculpt the character's form and separate them from the background.\n3.  **Hair Rendering (CRITICAL):** Hair MUST be rendered as individual, high-fidelity 3D hair strands with realistic texture, shine, and shadow. Flat, simple, or 'helmet-like' hair is strictly forbidden.\n4.  **Materials & Textures:** Employ physically-based rendering (PBR) for all materials. Skin should have subsurface scattering, clothing should show fabric weave and texture, and any metallic or leather surfaces must have realistic specular highlights and reflections.\n\n**Likeness (Absolute Priority):**\n-   Despite the high-end 3D conversion, the final character must be unmistakably recognizable as the person in the original photograph. Their core facial structure and features must be preserved with extreme fidelity.\n\n**Background:** Re-imagine the original background as a cinematic, high-detail 3D environment that fits the Final Fantasy aesthetic. It should be slightly out of focus to keep the emphasis on the character.\n\n**NEGATIVE PROMPTS:** 2D, painting, drawing, illustration, cartoon, anime, cel-shading, flat shading, low-poly, simple lighting, flat textures, blurry, plastic skin, keeping the original photo style.";
                    else if (hasCustomPrompt) finalPrompt = `**CRITICAL TASK: Reverse Cosplay Transformation based on User Prompt.**\n\n**Goal:** Create a new, original character that embodies the distinct art style of the specified creator or series ("${options.customPrompt}"), and draw this character as if they are cosplaying as the person in the provided photo.\n\n**User Prompt (ABSOLUTE TOP PRIORITY):** The user has specified a style source, which could be an author's name (e.g., 'Akira Toriyama'), a manga/anime title (e.g., 'Slam Dunk'), or a studio (e.g., 'Studio Ghibli'): "${options.customPrompt}".\n\n**Execution Hierarchy (Strictly Follow):**\n1.  **Base Character & Art Style (Most Important):** You are NOT drawing a specific pre-existing character unless one is explicitly named by the user. Instead, you MUST invent a NEW, ORIGINAL character whose face, features, and overall design look like they were authentically created by the specified author or for the specified series. The entire art style (linework, shading, coloring, eye shape) MUST perfectly match the source material from "${options.customPrompt}".\n\n2.  **Body Proportions (CRITICAL):** The body proportions (e.g., height, build, limb length) of the character MUST match the typical proportions found in the source material of "${options.customPrompt}". You are fitting the pose, clothing, and hairstyle from the photo onto a character that authentically belongs to the specified art style's world.\n\n3.  **Cosplay Elements (Copied from the Photo/Illustration - NON-NEGOTIABLE):** The character(s) must be depicted wearing the exact clothing and hairstyle, and holding the same pose and expression as the person(s) in the provided reference image. You are essentially putting the specified character into the "costume" of the person in the photo. Every detail below MUST be copied.\n    -   **Pose & Stance (CRITICAL):** Must be identical to the pose in the reference image.\n    -   **Clothing & Costume (CRITICAL):** Must be identical to the clothing in the reference image.\n    -   **Hairstyle (ABSOLUTELY CRITICAL):** Must be identical to the hairstyle in the reference image. This includes its color, length, and specific style (e.g., ponytail, short hair, bangs). This is a top-priority cosplay element.\n    -   **Expression (CRITICAL):** Must be identical to the expression in the reference image.\n    -   **Props & Accessories:** Must include any props or accessories from the reference image.\n\n4.  **Final Result:** The final image should clearly look like "a character from the world of '${options.customPrompt}' is cosplaying as the person from the photo".\n\n**BACKGROUND:** Generate a simple, thematic background that fits the world of "${options.customPrompt}".\n\n**NEGATIVE PROMPTS:** drawing the person from the photo, keeping the original character's clothing, keeping the original character's pose, a simple style transfer, photograph, realistic.`;
                    else finalPrompt = `**CRITICAL TASK: Convert this photograph into a unique 'Realism-Manga Hybrid' style.**\n\n**STYLE:** The goal is a hybrid art form that combines the detailed line art of Japanese manga with the textured, realistic coloring of a digital portrait painting.\n\n**EXECUTION HIERARCHY (Follow in order):**\n1.  **Manga Line Art (Foundation):** First, convert the subjects from the photograph into a layer of clean, professional, **black-and-white manga line art**.\n    -   **Line Style (CRITICAL):** The line art must be extremely **thin and delicate**. Use consistently thin, sharp lines to capture fine features, hair strands, and fabric textures. Avoid thick, bold, or overly expressive line weight variations.\n\n2.  **Realistic Coloring (The Layer Beneath):** Apply color **underneath** the line art layer using a painterly, realistic aesthetic that mimics a digital portrait of a real person.\n    -   **Technique & Brushwork:** Use a digital painting technique that emphasizes realistic skin tones, textures, and soft blending. While some brushstroke texture is good, the primary goal is a smooth, lifelike appearance for the skin and features.\n    -   **Color Palette:** Use a slightly desaturated color palette to give the image a calm, sophisticated, and less vibrant feel. Avoid overly bright or intense colors.\n    -   **Lighting & Shading:** Replicate realistic lighting and shadows to create depth and form, as one would in a realistic portrait painting. The light should interact with the subject naturally.\n\n3.  **Final Combination:** The final image must clearly show the delicate black manga lines on top of the realistically painted colors. The two styles should complement each other to create a unique, high-quality illustration.\n\n**Likeness:** It is absolutely critical to maintain the likeness and core facial structure of all subjects from the original photograph. They must remain clearly recognizable.\n\n**Background:** Re-render the original background with a soft, painterly, and slightly desaturated look that complements the hybrid style.\n\n**NEGATIVE PROMPTS:** thick lines, bold lines, heavy outlines, cel-shading, flat colors, anime coloring, cartoonish, 3D, photograph, blurry, overly saturated colors, sketch.`;
                } else { // illustration
                    if(transformType === 'realistic') finalPrompt = "**CRITICAL TASK: Photorealistic Re-imagining.**\n\n**Goal:** Transform the provided illustration into a high-quality, photorealistic image. The final output should look like a real-world photograph of a person who is the realistic counterpart of the character.\n\n**Likeness & Proportions (ABSOLUTE PRIORITY):**\n1. **Recognizability:** The person in the final photograph MUST be instantly recognizable as the character from the original illustration. Preserve their core hairstyle, clothing, and pose.\n2. **Realistic Proportions (CRITICAL ADJUSTMENT):** While maintaining recognizability, you MUST adjust the character's facial features (eyes, nose, mouth) and facial structure to match realistic human proportions. Do not strictly adhere to the original illustration's potentially stylized proportions. The goal is to create a believable, real-world human face that is the realistic counterpart of the illustrated character.\n\n**Execution Steps (Photorealism):**\n- **Skin:** Render with realistic skin texture, including pores, subtle imperfections, and natural lighting.\n- **Hair:** Render with realistic hair, showing individual strands, natural shine, and shadows.\n- **Materials:** Clothing and accessories must have believable, real-world textures (e.g., fabric weave, leather grain).\n- **Lighting:** Apply professional, cinematic lighting that enhances the realism and creates a dramatic mood.\n\n**Background:** Re-render the original background in a photorealistic style. Enhance its details, lighting, and textures to match the realism of the character.\n\n**NEGATIVE PROMPTS:** painting, animation, manga, illustration, drawing, cartoon, anime, 3D, CGI, plastic skin, blurry, keeping original cartoon proportions.";
